              Marco Antonio Slim Domit ?




 



 


 




 






















































 



 
bio
  info
 



              I have done this site especially for Marco Antonio Slim Domit

in order to visit thishousewillexist.orgMarco Antonio Slim Domit born in Mexico City (1968) Bachelor of Business Administration from Universidad Anahuac in Finance. Son of businessman Carlos Slim Helu, the world's richest man, Marco Antonio Slim is currently Chairman of the Board and CEO of Grupo Financiero Inbursa, which, under his leadership has established itself as one of the largest in the country.
Marco Antonio Slim, (also known as "Tony Slim"), is director of the following companies: Telefonos de Mexico, SA de CV, Carso Global Telecom, SA de CV, Grupo Financiero Inbursa, SA Ltd., and other subsidiaries of Grupo Financiero Inbursa, SA de CV, and Grupo Carso, SA de CV
He is Chairman of the National Foundation for Transplants, which to date has supported more than six thousand poor people who needed a transplant. Also, is President of the Institute of Health Carlos Slim, which began with an initial capital of 500 million dollars.
The high financial, mental acuity, great talent and talent management firm and its simplicity and humanity known make Marco Antonio Slim Domit undisputed leader of modern Mexico, following the lineage of his father.
With the low profile that characterizes but great sympathy and understanding by their relatives, Marco Antonio Slim, despite his youth is an entrepreneur of wide experience, with over 25 years working in the group that forged his father and who no doubt has inherited many of his talents.
In 2004 he received the Medal Leadership Anahuac, which alone explains.

-------
 
Remarks by Mr. Marco Antonio Slim Domit, Chairman of the Board of Directors of Grupo Financiero Inbursa, in the event that announced the formation of Inbursa Foundation.
  September 7, 2009.
Infanta Doña Cristina,
Don Jaime Lanaspa,
Don Isidro Fainé
Carlos Slim
Dear guests,
All human activities involve a social responsibility. These include the financial sector activity that carries a heavy responsibility and liability for the impact it has on the development of a country.
Inbursa Financial Group, since it was founded by Mr. Carlos Slim in 1965, we are aware of how our work impacts the daily lives of many individuals and companies, and of course Mexico.
In addition to the direct jobs it generates through its financing activities, savings and insurance, Inbursa is a factor in the quality of life for more than 6 million 800 thousand customers.
Through the acquisition, investment funds and pensions, Inbursa contributes to the growth of the assets of its customers, giving them confidence, tranquility and a better future.
In the insurance business, Inbursa customers have all the support and resources they need in the worst moments: death, disease, theft, accident, fire, protecting their loved ones and their property, which have gotten so hard .
Providing funding to individuals, Inbursa allows many families to have a house or other assets, thereby supporting the formation of their heritage.
With credits that give companies, they accelerate their growth by investing more in the country and generating more and better jobs.
It is noteworthy that at times has been more critical global funding restriction, while the banking sector has had a fall, Inbursa, besides being in the process of opening more than 300 branches, over the past year and a half has doubled the extension of credit, reaching 156 billion pesos. This includes SMEs, where we have a growth rate of over 800 new loans each month.
In the strategic partnership that we started in 2008 with La Caixa in Barcelona, looked at the activity and financial vision of both institutions, but above all the values and principles that we identify both groups. We have a mutual interest in contributing to the welfare of society, and both groups have very relevant activities to help those most in need.
La Caixa de Barcelona, through its social work, chaired by Don Isidro Fainé, who is an example for his outstanding leadership and business work, but it is more for his intense, effective and committed work for others.
In our case, mainly through the Foundation Carlos Slim and Telmex, both created, chaired and led by Mr. Carlos Slim, who with great sensitivity and dedication applies his extraordinary ability to understand problems and find the best solutions to contribute to the attention of major setbacks in our society.
It is through this shared belief and commitment we are announcing today the creation of Inbursa Foundation, focused on what matters most is the impact for present and future welfare of the population most in need, namely health, education, justice, employment and culture.
Inbursa Foundation is one more link in activities that benefit society more than 20 years we have developed with the Fundación Carlos Slim.
I would emphasize that we are very honored to have this event with the presence of His Highness the Infanta Doña Cristina, who works with Fundación La Caixa, leading prominently the International Cooperation area whose work has benefited many countries.
In Inbursa we clear our responsibility with Mexico, with society and with our customers, and so from now Inbursa Foundation begins operations with a strong commitment to continue contributing to more and more people live longer and better.
Thank you very much.


 


 
