Biography
Native of Mexico and heir to the Slim Helu fortune. Father, Carlos Slim Helu founded Grupo Carso in 1965; the holding company that currently has interests in telecommunications, construction, mining, retail, food and tobacco. Subsidiaries include America Movil, Grupo Financiero Inbursa, Impulsora del Desarrollo y Empleo en America Latina (IDEAL), Inmuebles Carso and Minera Frisco. Marco Antonio Slim Domit obtained a degree in Business Administration from the Universidad Anahuac and joined the family business upon graduation. Was appointed Chairman of Grupo ...
