Philanthropy

Giving Profile: Generous philanthropic giver who supports health, education and social projects. Slim Domit appears to be active in the family foundation, the Fundacion Carlos Slim Helu, established in 1986; in 2011, the private foundation had more than $2.89 billion in assets; total giving exceed $54 million. Father, Carlos Slim Helu endowed the foundation with $2 billion from dividends earned in 2006 and another $2 billion in 2010. To date, the foundation reportedly serves more than 29 million people worldwide. Slim Domit also serves as President of the Instituto Carlos Slim de la Salud, an initiative dedicated to medical research; in 2011 had more than $429 million in assets, and total giving exceed $52 million. The institute was founded in 2007 and is operated by Fundacion Carlos Slim Helu. Slim Domit also appears to support the Instituto Carlos Slim de la Educacion; in 2011, the private foundation had more than $1 million in assets and supports educational causes. He also supports various causes through Fundacion Inbursa, the philanthropic arm of Grupo Financiero Inbursa; in 2011, the foundation had more than $50 million in assets; total giving exceed $1.4 million.

